don't push the stashes if there isn't any

If you did a `git fire` in a repo without any stash you would get this error:
```
fatal: ambiguous argument 'stash': unknown revision or path not in the working tree.
Use '--' to separate paths from revisions, like this:
'git <command> [<revision>...] -- [<file>...]'
```

 * Don't die in a fire if your pre-commit hooks fail

BUG: Remove quotes to allow for more than one loop try.

The quotes around the remote name will make the spaces be retained and
hinder the looping.
See https://github.com/koalaman/shellcheck/wiki/SC2066.

BUG: Adjusting array expansion to use concatenation. SC2124.

Arrays can be handled different and using concatenation makes it more
portable in that regard.
See https://github.com/koalaman/shellcheck/wiki/SC2124.

BUG: Adding quotes to test. SC2086.

As $1 might trick the test quotes are safer to add in this part.
See https://github.com/koalaman/shellcheck/wiki/SC2086.

BUG: Add quoting. SC2046.

Adding quotes to the variable used in the command for new branch. There
are no guarantees that the branchname is properly formatted.
See https://github.com/koalaman/shellcheck/wiki/SC2046.

BUG: Use printf instead of echo. SC2028.

Silences shellcheck warning SC2028 about outputting format characters
with echo.
See https://github.com/koalaman/shellcheck/wiki/SC2028.
